! Reference

!! Frontmatter fields produced

| !Field | !Type | !Notes |
| `type` | string | Always `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` — drives the frontmatter deserializer |
| `msg-subject` | string | Empty when the email has no subject |
| `msg-from` | string | Display form (`Name <addr@x>`) when available, otherwise the raw address |
| `msg-to` | YAML list | One scalar per recipient — split on `,` and `;` |
| `msg-cc` | YAML list | Same as to-list; empty list when none |
| `msg-bcc` | YAML list | Same as to-list; usually empty for received mail |
| `msg-date` | ISO-8601 | UTC; falls back to `parsedDate` when `date` is missing |
| `msg-message-id` | string | `<…@server>` form; empty if not present |
| `msg-in-reply-to` | string | Same shape as message-id; empty for top-level messages |
| `msg-has-attachments` | yes/no | Includes inline images |
| `msg-quarantined-attachments` | YAML list | Only present when at least one attachment was blocked |
| `tags` | string | Single tag `email` for filtering |

!! Pipeline step reference

| !Step | !Type | !Output | !Artifact |
| `convert` | command | stdout (captureStdout) | `.email` of `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` |
| `attachments` | command | scanDir of `_derived/<basename>/` filtered by `att_` prefix | `.attachments/<filename>` of `attachment` type |
| `summary` | llm (auto) | LLM response text | `.summary` of `text/x-markdown` — only when `$:/config/rimir/msg-import/llm-summary == yes` |

!! Runner actions

```json
{
  "convert-msg-body": {
    "command": ".venv/bin/python3 plugins/rimir/msg-import/scripts/extract.py --mode=body --input {{input}} --attach-dir {{output}} --source-uri {{canonical_uri}}",
    "params": ["input", "output"]
  },
  "extract-msg-attachments": {
    "command": ".venv/bin/python3 plugins/rimir/msg-import/scripts/extract.py --mode=attachments --input {{input}} --attach-dir {{output}} --source-uri {{canonical_uri}}",
    "params": ["input", "output"]
  }
}
```

`.venv/bin/python3` resolves relative to `$tw.boot.wikiPath` (the runner's cwd), i.e. `dev-wiki/.venv/`. Replace with system `python3` if your install puts `extract-msg` system-wide instead.

`{{canonical_uri}}` is a built-in template variable added by file-pipeline 0.1.9 alongside `{{input}}` and `{{output}}` — it resolves to the parent tiddler's `_canonical_uri`. The extractor uses it to compute served URLs for inline images and attachments, so the same pipeline works across any file-upload location (default `/files/`, orga-apps' `/work/`, custom locations).

`{{input}}` and `{{output}}` are auto-quoted by `pipeline-executor.js` — no further escaping is needed. Other params are NOT auto-quoted by the runner; this plugin avoids using them.

!! Config tiddlers

| !Tiddler | !Default | !Effect |
| `$:/config/rimir/msg-import/llm-summary` | `no` | Enable the `.summary` LLM step |
| `$:/config/rimir/msg-import/quarantine-executables` | `yes` | Read by the Python script via env (defaults to on); set to `no` and pass `--allow-executables` if you really need them |

!! Python extractor CLI

```
extract_msg.py --mode={body|attachments}
               --input <abs-path-to-.msg>
               --attach-dir <dir-or-prefix-path>
               [--allow-executables]
```

* `--mode=body` writes inline-image files (cid:) to `--attach-dir` and emits frontmatter+markdown to stdout.
* `--mode=attachments` writes non-inline attachments to `--attach-dir` and emits a JSON summary to stdout.
* `--attach-dir` is interpreted as a directory when it ends with `/` (or already exists as a dir), otherwise as a `<dir>/<filename-prefix>` pair.
